  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And then a decree came, eventually, that all the Jews will be-- have to be assembled, and being transported.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And here, some miracle happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "This gentleman warned us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And he-- and he was going to try to save us, because he was a good friend of the family.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And even those who were already-- already involved in that movement, did not exactly knew what the consequences are going to be and how the Jews are going to deal-- how they're going to be dealt with.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "They hadn't an idea-- the final solution-- all these plans of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] --on one incident, what I believe happened, all the Jews have to assemble.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had to go be taken away.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we knew a Jewish doctor who put a decree on the door, on a house.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There's a typhoid in this house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if a typhoid victim-- person will be taken on a transport, it can inflict everybody else with a disease, and it will be a epidemic.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what happened was, is-- my sister Edith supposed to have typhoid.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a make-believe story-- typhoid.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And a big placard had been put in front of our door.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they came to take us away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They've been taken away to the juden-- to the vatican, what is also like a Jewish district.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from there-- from there, they were assembled and decided on which transport to go.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this man was-- possibly the doctor and other people-- managed to persuade the people who were going to-- on a-- on a train, that this girl has got typhoid, and if she goes on there-- with a certificate from the doctor-- if she's going to go on that train, an epidemic will be develop.",
      "word_count": 55
    }
  ],
